  "text": "As described in Section III, the input variables of a function can be partitioned into symmetric classes. The variables in a symmetric class have the same properties. During the canonical form computation, a symmetric class is handled as a single variable, resulting in the dramatic reduction of the complexity of the algorithm. This method was adopted in several algorithms [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] , but the correctness is not proven.",
